wikipedia.title: Black-headed sugar ant
wikipedia.summary: The black-headed sugar ant (Camponotus nigriceps), also known as the brown sugar ant, is a species of Formicinae ant endemic to Australia.

wikipedia.title: Myrmecia (ant)
wikipedia.summary: Myrmecia is a genus of ants first established by Danish zoologist Johan Christian Fabricius in 1804.
